		<!-- message -->
		<div>This is my understanding of how I think it works.<br />
<br />
I think when you do a successful FD one of two things can happen. One is the common result and one is the rare result.<br />
<br />
1. (common) You stay on the hatelist but only have a hate of 1.<br />
<br />
2. (rare) the mob completely mem-wipes you from its hatelist. The fact this happens sometimes lets you lose aggro on mobs even if they havn't reset at their spawn point. Just keep FDing over and over and one FD is bound to mem-wipe the mob eventually.<br />
<br />
Also, most mobs typically mem-wipe when they return to their spawn point, if they have one (but not always).</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
